description:
&lt;p&gt;Sue Ryder Thorpe Hall Hospice, Peterborough are looking for experienced and flexible Nursing Assistants to join their team of bank staff to work on the inpatient unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a range of support to patients and their families including inpatient care in our 20 bed hospice, a day service for those with long-term conditions and support in the community through our befriending, Hospice at Home and bereavement services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will be able to cover shifts at short notice and be willing to maintain any mandatory training required (support provided). It is important to note that at times the Hospice experiences a low number of patients and shifts will not always be available. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The suitable applicant will have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•             At least 1 year experience in a care setting (palliative care experience highly desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•             Numeracy and literacy skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•             IT skills including accessing the internet, email and word&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•             Good communication skill&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•             Experience of working within a team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•             Flexibility and available at short notice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• **Competitive enhanced pay for nights (30%), weekends (45%) and public holidays (60%)**&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• *Continuation of NHS pension*&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• *Mileage paid*&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Company pension scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Paid qualifications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Corporate discount with hundreds of retailers and services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Staff discount of 15% on new goods online at shop.sueryder.org&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Cash referral bonus scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Online Wellbeing Centre&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Free Will writing service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Free onsite parking&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Free uniform&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Carers leave policy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Subsidised onsite meals and drinks&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Structured induction programme and learning and development opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whether we’re supporting people in the hospice or their own homes, our focus is on quality of life – giving every patient the care and support they need to spend the time they have left in the way they choose.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sue Ryder reserve the right to remove this advert before the closing date if a sufficient number of candidates have been received.&lt;/p&gt;
